  "prompt": "How can I apply for a job in Modeling at Dreamworks?",
  "response": "To apply for a modeling job at DreamWorks Animation:\n\n1. Visit the official DreamWorks Animation careers website\n(www.dreamworksjobs.com or careers.nbcuniversal.com)\n\n2. Search for specific modeling or 3D artist positions in their job listings\n\n3. Prepare a strong portfolio that demonstrates:\n- 3D modeling skills\n- Character design experience\n- Proficiency in relevant software (Maya, ZBrush, etc.)\n- Animation or character creation expertise\n\n4. Typical requirements often include:\n- Bachelor's degree in Animation, Computer Graphics, or related field\n- Proven experience in 3D modeling\n- Strong technical and artistic skills\n- Proficiency in industry-standard software\n\n5. Optional steps:\n- Network on LinkedIn\n- Attend animation/gaming industry job fairs\n- Follow DreamWorks' social media for job postings\n- Consider internship opportunities\n\n6. Submit online application with:\n- Updated resume\n- Portfolio/demo reel\n- Cover letter highlighting relevant skills\n\n7. Be prepared for potential skills assessment or interview process\n\nTips: Ensure your portfolio showcases high-quality, professional work that aligns with DreamWorks' animation style.",
